-- Ford’s FCE Bank Said to Price 2017 Bonds to Yield 4.825%
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-02-08T11:29:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/ford-s-fce-bank-said-to-price-2017-bonds-to-yield-4-825-.html
FCE Bank Plc’s sale of bonds due in
February 2017 will be priced to yield 4.825 percent, according
to a banker with knowledge of the transaction. FCE Bank, a unit
of  Ford Motor Co. (F) , is issuing 250 million pounds of bonds.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  